# XCloak Documentation

Welcome to the XCloak docs. XCloak is an open-core enterprise security platform combining NGFW, SIEM, EDR, SOAR, and MDM capabilities in a single Go/PostgreSQL/Flutter stack.

**Quick links:**
- [Getting Started](#getting-started) — up and running in 5 minutes
- [Deployment Guide](#deployment-guide) — production setup with Kubernetes/Helm
- [Go Agent](#go-agent) — Linux and Windows endpoint agent
- [Mobile MDM Agent](#mobile-mdm-agent) — Android device management
- [Detection & Rules](#detection-and-rules) — Sigma, YARA, IOC, behavioral engines
- [SOAR & Playbooks](#soar-and-playbooks) — automated response
- [API Reference](#api-reference) — REST API overview
- [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting) — common issues and fixes

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

| Tool | Version | Required for |
|------|---------|-------------|
| Go | 1.21+ | Backend + agent |
| PostgreSQL | 16 | Primary database |
| Redis | 7+ | Rate limiting + sessions |
| Docker | 24+ | Observability stack (Kafka, Prometheus, Grafana, MinIO) |
| Flutter | 3.24.5 | Mobile agent (optional) |
| Java | 21 | Flutter Android build (optional) |

### 5-Minute Local Setup

**Step 1 — Clone the repo:**

```bash
git clone https://github.com/The-Abhishek1/XCLOAK-SECURITY-SUITE.git
cd XCLOAK-SECURITY-SUITE
```

**Step 2 — Start infrastructure:**

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

This starts PostgreSQL, Redis, Kafka, Prometheus, Grafana, and MinIO. Access:
- Grafana: http://localhost:3001 (admin/xcloak)
- Prometheus: http://localhost:9090
- Kafka UI: http://localhost:8090
- MinIO Console: http://localhost:9001

**Step 3 — Configure the backend:**

```bash
cd xcloak-ngfw/backend
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` and set at minimum:
```env
JWT_SECRET=<output of: openssl rand -hex 32>
METRICS_TOKEN=<output of: openssl rand -hex 32>
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USER=xcloak
DB_PASSWORD=your_password
DB_NAME=ngfw
```

**Step 4 — Start the backend:**

```bash
# With hot reload (install: go install github.com/air-verse/air@latest)
air

# Or plain
go run ./main.go
```

The backend runs 56 database migrations automatically on first start. Migration 056 seeds 43 production-ready Sigma rules.

**Step 5 — Start the frontend:**

```bash
cd xcloak-ngfw/frontend
npm install && npm run dev
```

Open http://localhost:3000. The first user to sign up becomes the admin.

---

## Deployment Guide

### Docker Compose (Production)

Use `docker-compose.yml` for development and `docker-compose.dev.yml` for local development with hot-reload mounts.

For production, set all environment variables as secrets (not in the compose file). Use an external PostgreSQL and Redis rather than the bundled ones.

### Kubernetes with Helm

**Add the chart:**

```bash
# Install from this repo
helm dependency update charts/xcloak
helm install xcloak charts/xcloak \
  --namespace xcloak --create-namespace \
  --set global.ingress.host=xcloak.yourdomain.com \
  --set backend.env.JWT_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32) \
  --set backend.env.METRICS_TOKEN=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
```

**Minimal `values.yaml` for production:**

```yaml
global:
  ingress:
    host: xcloak.yourdomain.com

backend:
  replicaCount: 2
  env:
    JWT_SECRET: "your-secret-here"
    METRICS_TOKEN: "your-metrics-token"
    DB_HOST: "your-postgres-host"
    DB_USER: "xcloak"
    DB_PASSWORD: "your-db-password"
    DB_NAME: "ngfw"
    APP_DB_USER: "xcloak_app"
    APP_DB_PASSWORD: "your-app-user-password"
    REDIS_ADDR: "your-redis:6379"
    CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS: "https://xcloak.yourdomain.com"
    APP_BASE_URL: "https://xcloak.yourdomain.com"

postgresql:
  enabled: false  # Use external PostgreSQL

redis:
  enabled: false  # Use external Redis
```

**Bundled PostgreSQL and Redis (evaluation only):**

```yaml
postgresql:
  enabled: true
  auth:
    database: ngfw
    username: xcloak
    password: change_me

redis:
  enabled: true
  auth:
    enabled: false
```

> Kafka and MinIO are not bundled in the Helm chart — use external services or bring your own. Both degrade gracefully when unavailable.

