## Multi-Tenancy

### Self-Serve Signup

`POST /api/signup` provisions a new tenant + admin account. The first user who calls this becomes the platform admin. Subsequent signups create analyst accounts within the same tenant.

No SMTP is required for the initial signup. Email delivery is optional (configure `SMTP_*` env vars for password-reset emails).

### Tenant Isolation

Every resource (agent, alert, rule, playbook, integration, audit log) is scoped to a tenant via PostgreSQL Row-Level Security (RLS). The app pool connects as `xcloak_app` (DML-only role), and RLS policies enforce tenant isolation on every query.

A compromise of one tenant's API key cannot read another tenant's data — the isolation is enforced at the database level, not just the application layer.

### Custom Roles

Go to **Settings → Roles → New Role** to create a custom role. Permissions are additive:

| Permission | Grants |
|-----------|--------|
| `manage_firewall` | Create/edit/delete firewall rules |
| `manage_agents` | Enroll agents, rotate tokens, dispatch tasks |
| `manage_detection_rules` | Create/edit Sigma and YARA rules |
| `manage_threat_intel` | Add/edit/delete IOCs and threat feeds |
| `manage_playbooks` | Create and trigger playbooks |
| `manage_incidents` | Create/update/close incidents |
| `manage_users` | Create/edit/delete users |
| `manage_api_keys` | Issue and revoke API keys |
| `approve_soar_actions` | Approve/reject pending destructive tasks |
| `run_scripts` | Execute scripts on agents |
| `run_ai_analysis` | Trigger AI triage and memory dump analysis |
| `export_audit_logs` | Download audit log exports |
| `sync_firewall` | Push firewall rules to agents |

---

## Security Hardening

### Required Production Settings

```env
DB_SSLMODE=require             # or verify-full with a CA cert
APP_DB_PASSWORD=<strong-password>   # not the default "change_me_in_production"
JWT_SECRET=<64-char random hex>
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://xcloak.yourdomain.com  # exact origin only
APP_BASE_URL=https://xcloak.yourdomain.com
LOG_FORMAT=json
```

### TLS Configuration

XCloak can terminate TLS directly:
```env
TLS_CERT_FILE=/etc/ssl/xcloak/tls.crt
TLS_KEY_FILE=/etc/ssl/xcloak/tls.key
```

Or terminate at ingress/load balancer and run the backend on plain HTTP internally.

### Rate Limiting

Login endpoint: 10 requests per minute per IP.  
Username lockout: 5 failures per username triggers a 15-minute lockout.  
High-cost API endpoints (log search, export, dashboard): 120 requests per minute.

Rate limits use an atomic Lua sliding-window in Redis — no TOCTOU race.

### Audit Trail

All sensitive actions are logged to the `audit_logs` table and streamed to configured Splunk HEC endpoints in real time. Audit logs are batch-exported to MinIO under Object Lock (WORM) — they cannot be deleted even by an admin.

Export and verify:
```bash
# Check export status
curl https://xcloak.yourdomain.com/api/audit/export-status \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <admin-token>"
```

---

## API Reference

XCloak exposes a REST API on port 8080. All endpoints (except login and registration) require a valid JWT access token.

**Authentication:**
```bash
# Login
curl -X POST https://xcloak.yourdomain.com/api/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email": "admin@example.com", "password": "yourpassword"}'
# Returns: {"access_token": "eyJ...", "refresh_token": "eyJ..."}

# Use the token
curl https://xcloak.yourdomain.com/api/agents \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer eyJ..."
```

**Key endpoints:**

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | Login — returns access + refresh tokens |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/refresh` | Refresh access token (httpOnly cookie or body) |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/logout` | Revoke current session |
| `GET` | `/api/agents` | List enrolled agents |
| `GET` | `/api/agents/:id` | Agent detail with telemetry |
| `POST` | `/api/agents/:id/tasks` | Dispatch task to agent |
| `GET` | `/api/alerts` | List alerts (with filters) |
| `GET` | `/api/alerts/:id` | Alert detail with enrichment |
| `POST` | `/api/alerts/bulk-acknowledge` | Acknowledge multiple alerts |
| `GET` | `/api/incidents` | List incidents |
| `POST` | `/api/incidents` | Create incident |
| `GET` | `/api/sigma-rules` | List Sigma rules |
| `POST` | `/api/sigma-rules/import` | Import Sigma rule YAML |
| `GET` | `/api/yara/rules` | List YARA rules |
| `POST` | `/api/iocs/bulk` | Bulk import IOCs |
| `GET` | `/api/logs/search` | KQL log search |
| `POST` | `/api/mdm/enrollment-tokens` | Generate MDM enrollment token |
| `GET` | `/api/mdm/devices` | List enrolled mobile devices |
| `POST` | `/api/mdm/devices/:id/commands` | Dispatch MDM command |
| `GET` | `/api/metrics` | Prometheus metrics (requires METRICS_TOKEN) |
| `GET` | `/api/health` | Health check |
| `GET` | `/api/health/deep` | Deep health (DB, Redis, Kafka, ES) |

Full OpenAPI specification: `xcloak-ngfw/backend/docs/generated/openapi.yaml`

