## Integrations

### Slack

Go to **Settings → Integrations → Slack → Add**. Enter your Slack webhook URL and select the severity levels to notify. XCloak posts alert cards with severity color, rule name, and a link to the alert.

### Email

Go to **Settings → Notifications → Email**. Configure SMTP settings (`SMTP_HOST`, `SMTP_PORT`, `SMTP_USER`, `SMTP_PASSWORD`, `SMTP_FROM` in `.env`). Create rules per-severity in **Notifications → Email Rules**.

### PagerDuty

Go to **Settings → Integrations → PagerDuty**. Enter your integration key. XCloak creates PagerDuty incidents for critical/high severity alerts.

### Microsoft Teams

Go to **Settings → Integrations → Microsoft Teams**. Enter your Teams Incoming Webhook URL.

### Jira

Go to **Settings → Integrations → Jira**. Enter your Jira base URL, project key, and API token. XCloak auto-creates Jira issues from alerts/incidents.

### ServiceNow

Go to **Settings → Integrations → ServiceNow**. Enter your ServiceNow instance URL, username, and password. XCloak creates incidents via the Table API.

### Webhook

Go to **Settings → Integrations → Webhook**. Enter any HTTPS URL. XCloak POSTs JSON alert payloads. All outbound deliveries retry automatically (immediate → 5 s → 30 s) on transient failures.

### Active Directory / LDAP

Go to **Settings → Integrations → LDAP**. Enter your domain controller URL, bind DN, and password. XCloak auto-enriches every alert with user display name, department, and title from AD.

